ZH: 电车是一种方便的交通工具。
EN: Trams are a convenient mode of transportation.
ZH: 我们可以坐电车去市中心。
EN: We can take the tram to the city center.
ZH: 电车线路贯穿整个城市。
EN: The tram route runs through the entire city.
ZH: 电车上人们通常很多。
EN: There are usually a lot of people on the tram.
ZH: 我们坐电车去了游乐园。
EN: We took the tram to the amusement park.
ZH: 电车很环保，不会排放废气。
EN: Trams are environmentally friendly and do not emit exhaust fumes.
ZH: 我买了电车票，可以用来坐十站。
EN: I bought a tram ticket that is valid for ten stops.
ZH: 电车司机很耐心地等待老人上下车。
EN: The tram driver patiently waited for the elderly to board and alight.
ZH: 电车站离这里很近。
EN: The tram station is very close to here.
ZH: 我们从电车站步行回家。
EN: We walked back home from the tram station.
ZH: 我常常在电车上看书。
EN: I often read books on the tram.
ZH: 昨天我和朋友一起坐电车去看电影。
EN: Yesterday, my friends and I took the tram to watch a movie.
ZH: 电车突然停住了，可能发生了故障。
EN: The tram suddenly stopped, perhaps there was a malfunction.
ZH: 我喜欢坐电车欣赏沿途美景。
EN: I enjoy taking the tram to admire the scenery along the way.
ZH: 电车上的座位都被占满了。
EN: All the seats on the tram are taken.
ZH: 我今天迟到了，还差一站就能赶上电车。
EN: I am late today, I would have caught the tram if I missed one more stop.
ZH: 电车的速度较快，中途可以看到不同景色。
EN: Trams travel at a faster speed, allowing passengers to see different views along the way.
ZH: 我们要坐两次电车才能到达目的地。
EN: We need to take two trams to reach our destination.
ZH: 请在电车上保持安静，尊重他人。
EN: Please be quiet on the tram and respect others.
ZH: 电车是一种古老而又现代的交通工具。
EN: Trams are a combination of ancient and modern transportation.
